Data Structures

struct  DpuConfigs_t
 The structure is used to hold all the dpu configurations that were constructed at the time of pre-start configuration, so that they do not need to be reconstructed when issuing for the purpose of reconfiguration within sub-frame due to overlapping h/w resources (e.g HWA resources) within sub-frame among dpus or across sub-frames due to overlapping h/w resources (e.g HWA, L3 and core Local memory). Detailed Description

This section has a list of all the internal data structures which are a part of the DPC.

Typedef Documentation

typedef struct DpuConfigs_t DpuConfigs

The structure is used to hold all the dpu configurations that were constructed at the time of pre-start configuration, so that they do not need to be reconstructed when issuing for the purpose of reconfiguration within sub-frame due to overlapping h/w resources (e.g HWA resources) within sub-frame among dpus or across sub-frames due to overlapping h/w resources (e.g HWA, L3 and core Local memory).

Millimeter Object Detection DPC object/instance.

The structure is used to hold all the relevant information for the object detection DPC.

The structure is used to hold all the relevant information for each of the sub-frames for the object detection DPC.
